          <a name="intro" id="intro"></a>
          <h2>Introduction</h2>

          <p>Given a file <i>lu1.dat</i> (as stdin) from Seis88, 
          it generates a Grace project file showing rays and interfaces.</p>

	  <a name="details" id="details"></a>
          <h2>Description</h2>

          <p>Seis88 is a ray tracing modeling program. For each shot
          Seis88 records a file, generally called lu1.dat, containing
          model and rays information. Since Seis88 represents interfaces
          by cubic splines, it's trick to visualize the model.</p>

          <p>Grace is a plotting tool to display and manipulate 2D graphs.</p>

          <p>This menu processes a <i>lu1.dat</i> file from Seis88 to 
          produce a project file, which may be visualized with Grace.</p>

