          <a name="intro" id="intro"></a>
          <h2>Introduction</h2>

          <p>Given a file <i>lu1.dat</i> (as stdin) from Seis88, 
          it generates a Grace project file showing rays and interfaces.</p>

	  <!-- begin par -->
          <div class="parameters">

            <a name="par" id="par"></a>
            <h2>Parameters</h2>

            <p>The spatial window displayed is defined by the four following parameters.
            Only the maximum x coordinate is mandatory. The three others are safely guessed 
            from input file.</p>
	      
	    <!-- begin lst -->
            <ul>
              <li><span class="label">Minimum x coordinate (left corner)</span></li>

              <li class="req"><span class="reqlabel">Maximum x coordinate (right corner)</span></li>

              <li><span class="label">Minimum z coordinate</span></li>

              <li><span class="label">Maximum z coordinate</span></li>

              <li><span class="label">Turn off filling in of layers</span><br/>
              Whenever this flag is activated layers are not colorized.</li>

              <li><span class="label">Land color palette</span><br/>
              Specifies a color for first layer which resembles a rock instead of water.</li>

              <li><span class="label">File containing a custom palette</span><br/>
              Specifies a coustom palette to colorize layers</li>

              <li><span class="label">Display all rays in black</span></li>

              <li><span class="label">Suppress rays</span></li>

            </ul>
            <!-- end lst -->

          </div>
	  <!-- end par -->
	    
	  <a name="notes" id="notes"></a>
          <h2>Notes</h2>

          <p>The Grace project is sent to the standard output. Save
          it into a file with <i>.agr</i> extension, in order Grace
          recognizes it.</p>

	  <a name="credits" id="credits"></a>
          <h2>Credits</h2>
          <p>This program was written by Ricardo Biloti, Department of
          Applied Mathematics &ndash; State University of Campinas, as
          a project to turn Seis88 <i>user frendly</i>.</p>

